discussion_comments.comment_body:
This won't work when packaged and deployed, it needs to use either a root anchored path:
`const rootReadme = path.join(prompts.root, "README.md");

Or, if using `@turbo/workspaces` it can use the `paths.root` on the returned `Project` (this type can be seen [here](https://github.com/vercel/turbo/blob/main/packages/turbo-workspaces/src/types.ts#L24))

commented_code:
+const fs = require("fs").promises;
+
+const filePath = "../../../../../examples/basic/README.md";
+
+async function updateCommandsInREADME(selectedPackageManager) {
+  try {
+    // Read the content of the file
+    let data = await fs.readFile(filePath, "utf8");
+
+    // Replace all occurrences of 'pnpm' with selectedPackageManager
+    data = data.replace(/\bpnpm\b/g, `${selectedPackageManager} run`);

